10 Key Questions to Review Your B2B Lead Generation in 2026
B2B lead generation has never been more competitive, more complex, or more consequential. As we move deeper into 2026, the landscape is shifting faster than most marketing and sales teams can keep pace with. Buyer behavior has evolved. Privacy regulations have tightened. AI has infiltrated every stage of the funnel. And yet, many businesses are still running playbooks that were written for a market that no longer exists.

If your pipeline is underperforming, your cost-per-lead is climbing, or your sales team is complaining about lead quality, the problem may not be your team. It may be your strategy. The most successful B2B organizations in 2026 are not necessarily the ones with the biggest budgets. They are the ones asking the right questions and acting on honest answers.

This article is built for marketing leaders, demand generation managers, and revenue-focused executives who want to take a hard, clear-eyed look at what is working, what is not, and what needs to change. These ten questions are designed to stress-test your entire lead generation engine, from targeting and content to technology and measurement.

